<TEXT>

World stocks plunge on fears on US recession

<TIMEX3 tid="t1" type="DATE" value="2008-01-21">January 21, 2008</TIMEX3>

Stock prices dropped sharply in Europe and Asia <TIMEX3 tid="t2" type="DATE" value="2008-01-21">Monday</TIMEX3>, with fears of economic problems in the United States causing some of the biggest single-day losses in <TIMEX3 tid="t3" type="DATE" value="PAST_REF">recent years</TIMEX3>.

In Hong Kong, the Hang Seng index fell 5.5 percent-its biggest fall since the September 11, 2001, terrorist attacks.

Losses of between three and seven percent were recorded in India, China, Britain, France, Germany and Canada.

While there are many factors linking national economies, analysts blame <TIMEX3 tid="t4" type="DURATION" value="PAST_REF">recent</TIMEX3> losses on fears of a recession in the United States.

